          Jul 15, 2017                         - RelSci Data Update                

          Institutional Holdings Changes      




Background Information:


Vista Capital Partners, Inc. »
Vista Capital Partners' investment approach focuses on asset allocation, superior portfolio construction, low costs, tax-efficiency and disciplined rebalancing. The firm's investment process begins with the determination of the most appropriate, long-term asset allocation for each client. The firm then implements the asset allocation primarily using index funds. Vista Capital Partners seeks to construct investment portfolios that can deliver higher returns with less risk by focusing on investments in small-cap stocks and value stocks across the universe of US, international and emerging market equities. The firm adds bonds to their clients' portfolios to the extent the client's objective is capital preservation. Vista Capital Partners periodically rebalances portfolios to maintain risk at the appropriate level and to enhance returns.




